title: New SWAC membership announced
content_text: The Government gazetted today (December 8) the re-appointment of the Chairman and the appointment of three new members to the Social Welfare Advisory Committee for a period of two years.  Also, five incumbent members have been re-appointed to the Committee.  The re-appointment and appointments took effect on December 1, 2000. Mr Peter Wong Hong-yuen has extensive experience in community service and has been actively involved in the development of social welfare issues during his term as

involved in the development of social welfare issues during his term as 
      Chairman of the Committee over the past four years. The three new members are 
      Miss Dorothy Lau Wai-ling, the Director of Sheng Kung Hui Diocesan Welfare 
      Council; Mrs Cheung Ang Siew Mei, the Executive Director of Christian 
      Action; and Mr Keith Lam Hon-keung, the Chairman of Lai Bick Construction 
      and Investment Co. Ltd. The five incumbent

      years. They have all 
      participated actively in the work of the Committee during their terms of 
      office. The Secretary for Health

office. The Secretary for Health 
      and Welfare, Dr E K Yeoh, thanked all members for their valuable support 
      and contribution over the years.  He also welcomed the appointment of 
      the three new members to the Committee and looked forward to the 
      contribution of the Committee to the development of welfare services in 
      Hong Kong. The functions of the 
      Committee remain to keep social welfare services under continuous review 
      and to advise the Government on all policy issues relating to welfare
